## ABBREVIATIONS (key ones for reader reference)

- **BRP**: Bond Risk Premium (term premium)
- **CAY**: Consumption wealth ratio
- **C-P BRP**: Cochrane-Piazzesi Bond Risk Premium measure
- **DDM**: Dividend Discount Model
- **ERP**: Equity Risk Premium
- **ERPB**: ERP over Bond (Treasury)
- **ERPC**: ERP over Cash (T-bill)
- **HML**: High Minus Low (value factor)
- **IRP**: Inflation Risk Premium
- **K-W BRP**: Kim-Wright Bond Risk Premium measure
- **LtA**: Limits to Arbitrage
- **PEH**: Pure Expectations Hypothesis
- **SBRP**: Survey-based Bond Risk Premium
- **SDF**: Stochastic Discount Factor
- **SMB**: Small Minus Big (size premium)
- **TIPS**: Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities
- **UIP**: Uncovered Interest Parity
- **VMG**: Value Minus Growth (equity value premium)
- **VIX**: Implied volatility of S&P 500 index options

